Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.16,0:00:04.90,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,“在双发飞机可以越洋之前日子真难捱”
Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.16,0:00:04.90,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,"It'll be a cold day in hell before I let twins fly long-haul over-water routes."
Dialogue: 1,0:00:05.10,0:00:07.14,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,这话是Lynn Helms说的
Dialogue: 2,0:00:05.10,0:00:07.14,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Those were the words of Lynn Helms
Dialogue: 1,0:00:07.28,0:00:11.74,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,他是里根总统时期美国联邦航空管理局(FAA)的主管
Dialogue: 2,0:00:07.28,0:00:11.74,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,—administrator of the Federal Aviation Administration during the Reagan administration.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:12.04,0:00:16.56,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,那时候，美国的商业航班不允许双发飞机飞到
Dialogue: 2,0:00:12.04,0:00:16.56,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,At the time, no commercial american airplane with two engines was allowed to fly anywhere
Dialogue: 1,0:00:16.56,0:00:19.24,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,备降场以外六十分钟航程的距离以外
Dialogue: 2,0:00:16.56,0:00:19.24,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,farther than 60 minutes from a diversion airport.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:19.36,0:00:21.94,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,因为他们认为如果一台发动机失效
Dialogue: 2,0:00:19.36,0:00:21.94,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,The belief was that, if one engine failed,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:22.08,0:00:25.56,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,飞机只能安全地靠仅剩的一台发动机飞行一小时
Dialogue: 2,0:00:22.08,0:00:25.56,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,the other could only safely fly the plane for about an hour.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:25.66,0:00:29.24,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,但这个规则对小型飞机有很大的限制
Dialogue: 2,0:00:25.66,0:00:29.24,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,But this rule severely limited what smaller planes could do.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:29.36,0:00:31.78,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,以纽约到伦敦这种飞跃北大西洋的航线为例
Dialogue: 2,0:00:29.36,0:00:31.78,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,On North Atlantic routes like New York to London,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:31.86,0:00:34.94,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,双发飞机只能飞图中的区域
Dialogue: 2,0:00:31.86,0:00:34.94,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,twin-engine planes could only fly in these areas,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:35.06,0:00:37.00,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,但是不能飞这样的航线
Dialogue: 2,0:00:35.06,0:00:37.00,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,but a direct route looked like this.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:37.18,0:00:41.20,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,当年的解决方法要么是用双发绕远飞
Dialogue: 2,0:00:37.18,0:00:41.20,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,The options were to either fly a twin-engine plane on an inefficient routing,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:41.20,0:00:43.90,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,要么用费油的三发或四发飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:00:41.20,0:00:43.90,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,or fly a inefficient three or four-engine-plane.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:44.10,0:00:48.90,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,这样一来小飞机根本没法走更远一点的近路去飞小城市航线了
Dialogue: 2,0:00:44.10,0:00:48.90,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,There was no place for long-and-skinny routes between smaller cities using smaller planes,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:48.90,0:00:52.30,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,因为这些航线不允许航空公司用双发飞机飞
Dialogue: 2,0:00:48.90,0:00:52.30,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,since airline couldn't legally fly those smaller planes.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:52.40,0:00:56.80,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,这个简单的规则彻底改变了飞机的制造
Dialogue: 2,0:00:52.40,0:00:56.80,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,This one simple rule changed the very way airplanes were built.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:56.92,0:01:02.08,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,因为在60年代，这个60分钟的规定只用在双发飞机上
Dialogue: 2,0:00:56.92,0:01:02.08,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Now, in the 60's, this 60 minute regulation only applied to planes with two engines.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:02.22,0:01:05.68,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,那么飞机制造商当然可以制造四发飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:01:02.22,0:01:05.68,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Of course aircraft manufacturers could build quad-engine jets
Dialogue: 1,0:01:05.72,0:01:10.12,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,但它们必须足够大，保证机票能赚回油钱，航司才不会赔
Dialogue: 2,0:01:05.72,0:01:10.12,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,but those had to be huge for airlines to make their money's worth with their high fuel consumption.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:10.30,0:01:15.04,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,那时候747能拉400人
Dialogue: 2,0:01:10.30,0:01:15.04,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,The 747's of the time could carry more than 400 passengers.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:15.18,0:01:18.70,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,所以只能飞大客流量的航线
Dialogue: 2,0:01:15.18,0:01:18.70,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,They could therefore only fly on super high-demand routes
Dialogue: 1,0:01:18.70,0:01:21.94,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,比如纽约飞伦敦，每趟基本都满载
Dialogue: 2,0:01:18.70,0:01:21.94,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,like New York to London to have anyhope of being full.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:22.14,0:01:26.20,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,为了让稍微小一点的飞机也能方便的不间断越洋飞行
Dialogue: 2,0:01:22.14,0:01:26.20,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,In order to start flying more convenient non-stop routes from smaller markets,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:26.30,0:01:30.36,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,飞机得再小一点，又不能违反上面说的规定
Dialogue: 2,0:01:26.30,0:01:30.36,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,planes had to get smaller while still being legally allowed to hop the pond.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:30.48,0:01:32.60,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,于是三发飞机横空出世
Dialogue: 2,0:01:30.48,0:01:32.60,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,That's where trijets came into play.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:32.70,0:01:38.22,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,三发飞机同样不受上面的60分钟限制
Dialogue: 2,0:01:32.70,0:01:38.22,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,With three engines, these planes weren't subject to the same 60-minute regulation as twinjets.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:38.34,0:01:41.20,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,可以轻松飞大西洋航路
Dialogue: 2,0:01:38.34,0:01:41.20,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,They could easily fly any transatlantic route.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:41.30,0:01:45.50,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,所以在七八十年代，你在机场能看见的远程飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:01:41.30,0:01:45.50,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,That's why in the 70s or 80s, the long-haul jets you'd see at airpots were,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:45.50,0:01:49.60,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,绝大多数要么是747，要么是DC-10那样的三发飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:01:45.50,0:01:49.60,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,for the most part, either 747's or trijets like the DC-10.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:49.76,0:01:53.58,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,60分钟限制对跨大西洋飞行的确不方便
Dialogue: 2,0:01:49.76,0:01:53.58,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,This 60-minute regulation was inconvenient for Atlantic Crossings,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:53.70,0:01:58.32,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,但对于太平洋来说，这个规定却改变了夏威夷的发展
Dialogue: 2,0:01:53.70,0:01:58.32,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,but in the Pacific it actually changed how Hawaii developed.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:58.44,0:02:02.32,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,从加州到夏威夷没有任何备降场
Dialogue: 2,0:01:58.44,0:02:02.32,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,There are zero diversion airports between California and Hawaii,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:02.40,0:02:06.48,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,这远远大于上面提到飞机60分钟能飞的航程
Dialogue: 2,0:02:02.40,0:02:06.48,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,so the route isn't even close to covered under the 60-minute rule.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:06.56,0:02:11.62,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,结果就是，当年美国本土飞夏威夷只能用大飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:02:06.56,0:02:11.62,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,As a result, airlines could only fly huge planes between the mainland and Hawaii,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:11.78,0:02:15.26,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,也就是只能飞火奴鲁鲁
Dialogue: 2,0:02:11.78,0:02:15.26,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,which meant that planes could pretty much only fly to Honolulu.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:15.34,0:02:18.52,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,这直接导致夏威夷其他岛屿与美国本土没有任何航空连接
Dialogue: 2,0:02:15.34,0:02:18.52,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,There was virtually no service between the other islands and the mainland,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:18.52,0:02:20.90,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,导致它们很多都被荒废了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:18.52,0:02:20.90,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,which meant the other islands were severely isolated.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:21.12,0:02:26.36,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,这也是为啥最近这几年旅游业一直在开发夏威夷其他的岛屿
Dialogue: 2,0:02:21.12,0:02:26.36,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,That's part of the reason why the tourism industry only picked up on the other islands in recent decades.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:26.62,0:02:31.38,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,最初的时候60分钟限制其实是给活塞螺旋桨飞机定的
Dialogue: 2,0:02:26.62,0:02:31.38,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,The 60 minute rule originated from the days of piston driven propeller aircraft.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:31.56,0:02:35.72,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,因为那些破飞机发动机空中失效概率太高了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:31.56,0:02:35.72,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,With these, it was far more common for engines to just stop working mid-flight.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:35.94,0:02:37.98,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,所以总出事
Dialogue: 2,0:02:35.94,0:02:37.98,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,That's why there were contingency engines.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:38.06,0:02:42.64,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,但这条规则并没有因如今越来越可靠的喷气式发动机而改变
Dialogue: 2,0:02:38.06,0:02:42.64,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,The regulations just didn't adapt to the increased reliability of jet engines.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:42.98,0:02:49.72,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,数据显示每一台喷气式发动机失效，就有117台活塞发动机失效
Dialogue: 2,0:02:42.98,0:02:49.72,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Statistically, for every failure of a jet engine, there are 117 piston engine failures.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:49.86,0:02:54.08,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,当飞机进入喷气时代，发动机失效就不像当年那么吓人了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:49.86,0:02:54.08,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Once the jet age rolled in, engine failure just wasn't as much of a concern.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:54.16,0:02:58.44,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,所以在1985年，FAA终于“开恩”
Dialogue: 2,0:02:54.16,0:02:58.44,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,So, in 1985, the FAA begrudgingly granted permission
Dialogue: 1,0:02:58.44,0:03:04.92,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,让美国环球航空的双发飞机——波音767可以直飞波士顿到巴黎航线
Dialogue: 2,0:02:58.44,0:03:04.92,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,to Trans World Airlines to fly their twin-engined 767 direct between Boston and Paris
Dialogue: 1,0:03:05.04,0:03:09.28,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,这条航线上离备降场最远要飞120分钟
Dialogue: 2,0:03:05.04,0:03:09.28,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,—a route taking it up to 120 minutes away from diversion airports.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:09.36,0:03:14.12,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,这是FAA全新的规定的首例应用，称为“ETOPS”——
Dialogue: 2,0:03:09.36,0:03:14.12,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,This was the first example of a brand new FAA certification called ETOPS—
Dialogue: 1,0:03:14.24,0:03:17.52,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,全称“双发延程飞行”
Dialogue: 2,0:03:14.24,0:03:17.52,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,"Extended-range Twin-engine Operational Performance Standards",
Dialogue: 1,0:03:17.62,0:03:20.90,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,简言之“要么飞要么游”
Dialogue: 2,0:03:17.62,0:03:20.90,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,or more colloquially, "engines turn or passengers swim".
Dialogue: 1,0:03:21.04,0:03:23.76,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,航司在飞远程越洋航班之前
Dialogue: 2,0:03:21.04,0:03:23.76,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Before an airline can fly a long over-water route,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:23.82,0:03:27.28,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,他们得先买一架经过ETOPS认证的飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:03:23.82,0:03:27.28,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,they have to buy a plane with what's known as an ETOPS type rating.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:27.40,0:03:33.18,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,那些飞机安装有额外的通讯系统与灭火系统
Dialogue: 2,0:03:27.40,0:03:33.18,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Basically that means that the plane was built with adequate redundancies communications systems and fire suppression system
Dialogue: 1,0:03:33.18,0:03:35.44,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,以保证单发失效时的安全
Dialogue: 2,0:03:33.18,0:03:35.44,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,and fire suppression systems to fly safely if one engine fails.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:35.66,0:03:39.88,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,比如说，波音767——第一款得到ETOPS认证的机型
Dialogue: 2,0:03:35.66,0:03:39.88,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,For example, the 767—the first plane to get an ETOPS certification
Dialogue: 1,0:03:39.88,0:03:46.96,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,认证级别为ETOPS-180——最远可以飞离备降场180分钟航程的距离
Dialogue: 2,0:03:39.88,0:03:46.96,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,—has a type rating of 180 minutes meaning it can fly anywhere as long as its 180 minutes from a diversion airport.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:47.08,0:03:52.36,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,但航司拥有ETOPS认证的飞机不代表他们就能进行双发延程飞行
Dialogue: 2,0:03:47.08,0:03:52.36,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,But just because a plane has a type rating doesn't mean an airline can fly it ETOPS.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:52.46,0:03:56.76,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,他们还需要对飞机进行专门的维护，专门的机组、专门的乘务
Dialogue: 2,0:03:52.46,0:03:56.76,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,They have to have a special maintenance plan, a special flight crew, special cabin crew,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:56.76,0:04:01.02,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,专门的签派，专用的燃油以及特别定制的备降旅客安置方案
Dialogue: 2,0:03:56.76,0:04:01.02,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,special dispatchers, special fuel quantities, and special passenger recovery plans,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:01.02,0:04:05.20,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,因为光有一条备降的跑道是不够的
Dialogue: 2,0:04:01.02,0:04:05.20,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,since just because there's a runway doesn't mean that a plane can safely divert,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:05.28,0:04:09.00,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,飞机降落不代表紧急情况解除
Dialogue: 2,0:04:05.28,0:04:09.00,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,since the emergency doesn't end once the plane lands.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:09.18,0:04:11.36,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,比如说阿拉斯加的科尔德湾机场
Dialogue: 2,0:04:09.18,0:04:11.36,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Cold Bay, Alaska, for example,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:11.36,0:04:15.62,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,看上去的确是一个非常完美的亚洲飞北美航线的备降场
Dialogue: 2,0:04:11.36,0:04:15.62,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,is a perfect diversion airport for routes between Asia and North America.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:15.74,0:04:18.54,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,那个机场美洲只有六次商业航班
Dialogue: 2,0:04:15.74,0:04:18.54,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,It only has six commercial flights per week nowadays,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:18.54,0:04:22.00,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,而且那里之前有个空军基地，所以机场跑道非常长
Dialogue: 2,0:04:18.54,0:04:22.00,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,but as a former Air Force Base it has an enormous runway.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:22.14,0:04:28.32,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,可问题是科尔德湾那个小镇只有108人——太小了
Dialogue: 2,0:04:22.14,0:04:28.32,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,The only issue is that the town of Cold Bay has a population of 108—its tiny.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:28.32,0:04:33.48,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,要是有个飞机来备降，这镇子人口一下子能多一两倍
Dialogue: 2,0:04:28.32,0:04:33.48,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,So any diversions automatically double or triple the amount of people in the small town
Dialogue: 1,0:04:33.60,0:04:38.82,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,这尼玛连床都不够睡，碗筷都不够用
Dialogue: 2,0:04:33.60,0:04:38.82,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,There certainly aren't enough hotel rooms or restaurants to house and feed stranded passengers.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:38.82,0:04:42.94,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,所以航司如果最后决定备降科尔德湾机场
Dialogue: 2,0:04:38.82,0:04:42.94,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,So, if airlines plan to use Cold Bay as a diversion airport,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:42.94,0:04:48.80,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,就必须安排好旅客住哪、喂啥、怎么在48小时内送到目的地
Dialogue: 2,0:04:42.94,0:04:48.80,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,they need to make a plan for how to house, feed, and recover passengers within 48 hours of landing.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:48.92,0:04:53.54,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,去年美国航空公司一架波音787飞机，执飞上海到芝加哥航线
Dialogue: 2,0:04:48.92,0:04:53.54,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Last year an American Airlines 787 was flying from Shanghai to Chicago,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:53.54,0:04:57.16,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,中途在太平洋上空右发故障
Dialogue: 2,0:04:53.54,0:04:57.16,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,when its right engine had an issue halfway across the Pacific Ocean.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:57.20,0:05:00.30,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,飞机立刻左转备降科尔德湾机场
Dialogue: 2,0:04:57.20,0:05:00.30,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,The plane quickly took a left turn diverting to Cold Bay.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:00.42,0:05:04.00,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,当安排好降落的计划之后
Dialogue: 2,0:05:00.42,0:05:04.00,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Even before landing the plan was implemented,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:04.00,0:05:07.02,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,飞机上乘务发航班第二餐
Dialogue: 2,0:05:04.00,0:05:07.02,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,as flight attendants served a second meal service early.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:07.16,0:05:10.00,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,飞机安全降落科尔德湾机场后
Dialogue: 2,0:05:07.16,0:05:10.00,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Just a few hours after safely landing in Cold Bay,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:10.00,0:05:14.28,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,美国的机务即刻从西雅图飞往科尔德湾准备去修飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:05:10.00,0:05:14.28,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,American's mechanics took off from Seattle bound for Cold Bay to start fixing the plane.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:14.34,0:05:16.72,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,与此同时，阿拉斯加航空——美国航空公司的“友商”
Dialogue: 2,0:05:14.34,0:05:16.72,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,while Alaska Airlines, American's partner,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:16.72,0:05:20.20,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,从安克雷奇调遣一架波音737去接被困在科尔德湾的旅客们
Dialogue: 2,0:05:16.72,0:05:20.20,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,sent a 737 from Anchorage to pick up the stranded passengers.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:20.20,0:05:24.94,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,这时，乘务发了之前早已备好的航班第三餐
Dialogue: 2,0:05:20.20,0:05:24.94,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, flight attendants served the third set of meals they had stocked while waiting on the ground,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:25.00,0:05:28.08,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,同时美国海岸警卫队也为旅客们提供了取暖设备
Dialogue: 2,0:05:25.00,0:05:28.08,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,and the coast guard opened their heated hanger to passengers.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:28.22,0:05:32.52,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,备降十小时后，旅客就已经前往安克雷奇了
Dialogue: 2,0:05:28.22,0:05:32.52,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Just 10 hours after the emergency landing, passengers were on their way to Anchorage,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:32.52,0:05:36.78,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,在那过夜后，搭乘美国航空公司波音757继续前往芝加哥
Dialogue: 2,0:05:32.52,0:05:36.78,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,where they spent the night before taking an American 757 to Chicago.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:36.98,0:05:40.98,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,这是一个备降旅客安置里教科书般的例子
Dialogue: 2,0:05:36.98,0:05:40.98,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,That was a perfect example of how the passenger recovery plan worked.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:41.32,0:05:46.86,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,航司的快速反应以及完善的安置规划让旅客安全快速的完成了旅程
Dialogue: 2,0:05:41.32,0:05:46.86,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,The quick response and defined plan helped the airline get passengers out safely and quickly.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:47.06,0:05:51.14,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,现在，因为发动机的可靠、大量关键设备的冗余
Dialogue: 2,0:05:47.06,0:05:51.14,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Now, because of the solid engine reliability, numerous redundancies
Dialogue: 1,0:05:51.14,0:05:53.40,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,以及备降旅客安置计划的完善
Dialogue: 2,0:05:51.14,0:05:53.40,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,and well-designed passenger recovery plans,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:53.40,0:05:58.06,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,航空公司和一些机型可以获得一些非常非常长的ETOPS认证
Dialogue: 2,0:05:53.40,0:05:58.06,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,airlines and airplanes can now receive insane ETOPS certifications.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:58.10,0:06:04.88,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,刚刚备降科尔德湾的波音787梦幻客机，拥有ETOPS-330认证
Dialogue: 2,0:05:58.10,0:06:04.88,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,The 787 Dreamliner, the plane that diverted to Cold Bay, has a type rating of 330 minutes.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:05.00,0:06:09.62,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,也就是说可以飞离备降场最多五个半小时航程
Dialogue: 2,0:06:05.00,0:06:09.62,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,That means it can fly up to 5.5 hours away from a diversion airport.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:09.70,0:06:13.14,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,一些南半球的长途越洋航线
Dialogue: 2,0:06:09.70,0:06:13.14,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Certain routes over long-ocean stretches in the southern hemisphere
Dialogue: 1,0:06:13.18,0:06:16.54,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,过去只在理论上可以用四发飞机执飞
Dialogue: 2,0:06:13.18,0:06:16.54,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,were theoretically possible in the past with four engine planes,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:16.66,0:06:18.50,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,但经济上根本不允许
Dialogue: 2,0:06:16.66,0:06:18.50,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,but were economically impossible,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:18.50,0:06:24.32,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,因为比如墨尔本飞圣地亚哥，飞机根本坐不满，航空公司简直赔死
Dialogue: 2,0:06:18.50,0:06:24.32,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,since airlines could never fill the large planes on the low-demand city pairs like Melbourne to Santiago.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:24.42,0:06:26.86,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,但有了ETOPS-330认证
Dialogue: 2,0:06:24.42,0:06:26.86,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,With the ETOPS 330 certification,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:26.92,0:06:30.92,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,LATAM航空可以用非常省油的波音787
Dialogue: 2,0:06:26.92,0:06:30.92,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,LATAM Airlines can fly their small 787 economically
Dialogue: 1,0:06:30.92,0:06:34.20,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,在这条客流相对不大的航线上跨太平洋飞行（但仍可盈利）
Dialogue: 2,0:06:30.92,0:06:34.20,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,on this relatively low-demand route across the South Pacific.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:34.40,0:06:38.56,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,空客A350飞机甚至认证到了ETOPS-370
Dialogue: 2,0:06:34.40,0:06:38.56,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,The Airbus a350 is even rated for ETOPS 370
Dialogue: 1,0:06:38.56,0:06:42.78,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,最远可以到达远离备降场六小时十分钟的航程
Dialogue: 2,0:06:38.56,0:06:42.78,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,—it can fly 6 hours and 10 minutes away from diversion airports.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:42.88,0:06:48.28,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,这使得A350可以飞跃除了南极点之外地球的任何地方
Dialogue: 2,0:06:42.88,0:06:48.28,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,This plane can therefore fly everywhere on earth except directly over the South Pole.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:48.40,0:06:54.14,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,这条简单规定的改变让三发、四发飞机一下变成了历史
Dialogue: 2,0:06:48.40,0:06:54.14,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Because of this simple rule change three and four-engine planes are largely a relic of the past.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:54.14,0:06:59.08,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,波音和空客目前仍然生产的各自唯一的四发飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:06:54.14,0:06:59.08,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Boeing and Airbus' largest jets are both their only four engine planes in production
Dialogue: 1,0:06:59.18,0:07:01.22,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,就是747和A380
Dialogue: 2,0:06:59.18,0:07:01.22,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,—the 747 and a380
Dialogue: 1,0:07:01.32,0:07:05.36,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,如今北大西洋上几乎所有飞机都是双发的
Dialogue: 2,0:07:01.32,0:07:05.36,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Nearly all North Atlantic traffic today is on twin-engined planes,
Dialogue: 1,0:07:05.40,0:07:08.62,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,因为有越来越多的小飞机也可以获得ETOPS认证
Dialogue: 2,0:07:05.40,0:07:08.62,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,as smaller and smaller planes get ETOPS certifications.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:08.74,0:07:15.64,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,比如加拿大航空，用ETOPS认证的可爱的A319，最多拉120人
Dialogue: 2,0:07:08.74,0:07:15.64,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Air Canada, for example, flies their tiny 120 passenger a319 with ETOPS certification
Dialogue: 1,0:07:15.64,0:07:18.72,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,每天一班圣约翰机场到伦敦希思罗机场
Dialogue: 2,0:07:15.64,0:07:18.72,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,daily between St Johns Airport and London Heathrow.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:18.86,0:07:24.68,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,英国航空用更袖珍的A318,飞纽约到伦敦的航线
Dialogue: 2,0:07:18.86,0:07:24.68,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,British Airways even sends the even smaller a318 between New York and London City Airport.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:24.88,0:07:28.10,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,这些航线30年前简直无法想象
Dialogue: 2,0:07:24.88,0:07:28.10,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,These routes would have been unimaginable 30 years ago,
Dialogue: 1,0:07:28.10,0:07:30.42,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,但如今飞机的可靠性
Dialogue: 2,0:07:28.10,0:07:30.42,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,but the reliability of the airplanes of today
Dialogue: 1,0:07:30.42,0:07:34.54,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,使我们不用再为担心小飞机飞越大洋的安全性而担心
Dialogue: 2,0:07:30.42,0:07:34.54,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,mean that we need not fear flying small planes over big oceans.
